               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430130-name-1393" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1393" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1393" type="surname" value="JUDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1393" type="given" value="GEORGE WALKER"></interp>GEORGE WALKER JUDGE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a Thames-police inspector. About eight o'clock in the morning of the 21st of Jan., I was crossing the water from Prince's-stairs, and saw the prisoner in the after-room of a barge called the <hi rend="italic">Bill</hi>, belonging to Mr. Gammon—I saw him bring a tub of large coals, and put into his boat—I shot astern of the barge, and got into the boat—I told him to row me across the river—I showed these coals to Mr. Gammon, and he recognized them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430130-name-1394" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1394" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1394" type="surname" value="GAMMON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1394" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT GAMMON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am owner of this barge called the <hi rend="italic">Bill</hi>, and the coals in it—I have examined, and compared these, and believe them to be mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was working up the river, and asked a lighterman if I might have these coals in the barge; he said, "Stop a minute, and lend me a hand to pull this barge in, then you may have them." I had other coals in the boat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430130-name-1395" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1395" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1395" type="surname" value="JUDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1395" type="given" value="GEORGE WALKER"></interp>GEORGE WALKER JUDGE</persName>
                  </hi>. He did not say a word of this till he got half<lb></lb>way across the water—he had 50lbs. of other coals in the boat, but these were in the tub.</p>
